From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Victor Krook <victor.krook@everdrone.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] media: i2c: ov2640: default to YUYV and VGA for sun4i-csi

The sun4i-csi driver in this tree defaults its sink pad to YUYV
640x480, and link validation requires source and sink pad formats to
match. OV2640 defaults to UYVY and SVGA (800x600), which causes
pipeline validation to fail at STREAMON with -EPIPE ("Broken pipe").

Switch OV2640 defaults to YUYV8_2X8 and VGA (640x480) so the pipeline
can start without userspace media-graph format programming.

Signed-off-by: Victor Krook <victor.krook@everdrone.com>
---
 drivers/media/i2c/ov2640.c | 8 ++++----
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/media/i2c/ov2640.c b/drivers/media/i2c/ov2640.c
--- a/drivers/media/i2c/ov2640.c
+++ b/drivers/media/i2c/ov2640.c
@@ -1002,11 +1002,11 @@ static int ov2640_init_state(struct v4l2_subdev *sd,
 	struct v4l2_mbus_framefmt *try_fmt =
 		v4l2_subdev_state_get_format(sd_state, 0);
 	const struct ov2640_win_size *win =
-		ov2640_select_win(SVGA_WIDTH, SVGA_HEIGHT);
+		ov2640_select_win(VGA_WIDTH, VGA_HEIGHT);
 
 	try_fmt->width = win->width;
 	try_fmt->height = win->height;
-	try_fmt->code = MEDIA_BUS_FMT_UYVY8_2X8;
+	try_fmt->code = MEDIA_BUS_FMT_YUYV8_2X8;
 	try_fmt->colorspace = V4L2_COLORSPACE_SRGB;
 	try_fmt->field = V4L2_FIELD_NONE;
 	try_fmt->ycbcr_enc = V4L2_YCBCR_ENC_DEFAULT;
@@ -1210,8 +1210,8 @@ static int ov2640_probe(struct i2c_client *client)
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;
 
-	priv->win = ov2640_select_win(SVGA_WIDTH, SVGA_HEIGHT);
-	priv->cfmt_code = MEDIA_BUS_FMT_UYVY8_2X8;
+	priv->win = ov2640_select_win(VGA_WIDTH, VGA_HEIGHT);
+	priv->cfmt_code = MEDIA_BUS_FMT_YUYV8_2X8;
 
 	v4l2_i2c_subdev_init(&priv->subdev, client, &ov2640_subdev_ops);
 	priv->subdev.internal_ops = &ov2640_internal_ops;
--
2.43.0
